Now fix the code. The bug is in `getOffsetFromLocal`. The fix: change the condition from `(offsetLocal - offsetAdjusted) < 0` to `(offsetLocal - offsetAdjusted) > 0` and also adjust the logic inside. Actually, the typical fix is:

```
public int getOffsetFromLocal(long instantLocal) {
    final int offsetLocal = getOffset(instantLocal);
    final long instantAdjusted = instantLocal - offsetLocal;
    final int offsetAdjusted = getOffset(instantAdjusted);
    if (offsetLocal != offsetAdjusted) {
        if ((offsetLocal - offsetAdjusted) > 0) {
            long nextLocal = nextTransition(instantAdjusted);
            long nextAdjusted = nextTransition(instantLocal - offsetAdjusted);
            if (nextLocal != nextAdjusted) {
                return offsetLocal;
            }
        }
    }
    return offsetAdjusted;
}
```

This changes the comparison to `> 0` to handle fall-back (overlap) where offset decreases. For spring forward (offset increase), offsetLocal < offsetAdjusted, so condition false, and we return offsetAdjusted, which is the later offset, pushing the instant after the gap, which is correct.

